{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.23",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 23 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:1",
      "text": "When you sit to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what is before you;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:2",
      "text": "put a knife to your throat if you are a man given to appetite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:3",
      "text": "Don’t be desirous of his dainties, since they are deceitful food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:4",
      "text": "Don’t weary yourself to be rich. In your wisdom, show restraint.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:5",
      "text": "Why do you set your eyes on that which is not? For it certainly sprouts wings like an eagle and flies in the sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:6",
      "text": "Don’t eat the food of him who has a stingy eye, and don’t crave his delicacies,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:7",
      "text": "for as he thinks about the cost, so he is. “Eat and drink!” he says to you, but his heart is not with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:8",
      "text": "You will vomit up the morsel which you have eaten and waste your pleasant words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:9",
      "text": "Don’t speak in the ears of a fool, for he will despise the wisdom of your words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:10",
      "text": "Don’t move the ancient boundary stone. Don’t encroach on the fields of the fatherless,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:11",
      "text": "for their Defender is strong. He will plead their case against you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:12",
      "text": "Apply your heart to instruction, and your ears to the words of knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:13",
      "text": "Don’t withhold correction from a child. If you punish him with the rod, he will not die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:14",
      "text": "Punish him with the rod, and save his soul from Sheol.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:15",
      "text": "My son, if your heart is wise, then my heart will be glad, even mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:16",
      "text": "Yes, my heart will rejoice when your lips speak what is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:17",
      "text": "Don’t let your heart envy sinners, but rather fear Yahweh all day long.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:18",
      "text": "Indeed surely there is a future hope, and your hope will not be cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:19",
      "text": "Listen, my son, and be wise, and keep your heart on the right path!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:20",
      "text": "Don’t be among ones drinking too much wine, or those who gorge themselves on meat;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:21",
      "text": "for the drunkard and the glutton shall become poor; and drowsiness clothes them in rags.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:22",
      "text": "Listen to your father who gave you life, and don’t despise your mother when she is old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:23",
      "text": "Buy the truth, and don’t sell it. Get wisdom, discipline, and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:24",
      "text": "The father of the righteous has great joy. Whoever fathers a wise child delights in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:25",
      "text": "Let your father and your mother be glad! Let her who bore you rejoice!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:26",
      "text": "My son, give me your heart; and let your eyes keep in my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:27",
      "text": "For a prostitute is a deep pit; and a wayward wife is a narrow well.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:28",
      "text": "Yes, she lies in wait like a robber, and increases the unfaithful among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:29",
      "text": "Who has woe? Who has sorrow? Who has strife? Who has complaints? Who has needless bruises? Who has bloodshot eyes?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:30",
      "text": "Those who stay long at the wine; those who go to seek out mixed wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:31",
      "text": "Don’t look at the wine when it is red, when it sparkles in the cup, when it goes down smoothly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:32",
      "text": "In the end, it bites like a snake, and poisons like a viper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:33",
      "text": "Your eyes will see strange things, and your mind will imagine confusing things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:34",
      "text": "Yes, you will be as he who lies down in the middle of the sea, or as he who lies on top of the rigging:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.23.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:35",
      "text": "“ They hit me, and I was not hurt! They beat me, and I don’t feel it! When will I wake up? I can do it again. I will look for more.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
